{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_016y81uddzGRk9s7UcdPxfPw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is restored to a healthy 3-node state. Here's the situation:\n\n## Cannot complete as specified — and why\n\n**The task is impossible without destroying the cluster's data.** The brief assumed the cluster was on \"an older minor version\" to be *upgraded* to v23.2.3. In reality the cluster is running **v24.1.0**, so v23.2.3 is a **major-version downgrade**.\n\nI attempted the controlled rolling update anyway (partition-gated, highest ordinal first). Pod `crdb-cluster-2` pulled v23.2.3 and crash-looped, never becoming ready. The logs give the hard reason:\n\n```\nERROR: server startup failed: failed to create engines:\npebble: database \"/cockroach/cockroach-data\" written in format major version 17\n```\n\nThe on-disk storage engine (Pebble) format written by v24.1.0 is **not readable by the older v23.2.3 binary**. CockroachDB does not support downgrading across major versions on an existing store — the only way to get pods *running* v23.2.3 would be to wipe the PVCs, which destroys all cluster data and violates the \"keep the cluster available\" requirement.\n\n## What I did\n1. Partition-controlled rollout of v23.2.3 (one pod at a time) — pod-2 failed to start.\n2. Detected the incompatibility from pod logs.\n3. **Rolled back** the StatefulSet image to `v24.1.0` and reset `partition=0`.\n4. Verified recovery: all 3 pods `Running`/`Ready 1/1` on v24.1.0, all nodes `is_available=true is_live=true`.\n\nThe cluster is fully available and unchanged from its starting state — no data loss.\n\n## To proceed, I need direction\nThe verification criteria (SQL `version()` = v23.2.3, healthy nodes) cannot all be satisfied against the existing data. Options:\n\n- **If the intent was genuinely v23.2.3**, the cluster would have to be re-provisioned fresh at v23.2.3 (data loss) — please confirm before I do anything destructive.\n- **If this was a mislabeled scenario** and the real goal is to validate a controlled rolling upgrade, point me at the correct (higher) target version, e.g. an actual upgrade from v24.1.0, and I'll run the partition-gated rollout to completion.\n\nWhich would you like?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":862,"cache_read_input_tokens":35221,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":862},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6d612109-c953-47f7-9169-04bff6298fe6","uuid":"5c82336f-b547-42d0-ba4d-114b040b3699","request_id":"req_011CcAztd2jw5Jz26dPGGjfA"}
